LEFT JOIN. If you use INNER JOIN, customers with zero orders silently vanish from the report.

SELECT c.name, COUNT(o.id) AS order_count, COALESCE(SUM(o.total), 0) AS total_spend, MAX(o.created_at) AS last_order FROM customers c LEFT JOIN orders o ON c.id = o.customer_id GROUP BY c.id, c.name;

Note: COUNT(o.id) not COUNT(*). COUNT(*) would return 1 for customers with no orders because the LEFT JOIN row still exists.

